<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Evil, Problem of (Theodicy) on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/evidences/evil-problem-of-theodicy/</link><description>Recent content in Evil, Problem of (Theodicy) on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://christir.org/essays/evidences/evil-problem-of-theodicy/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>EVIL IN THE WORLD: IS GOD HOLY?</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/evidences/evil-problem-of-theodicy/evil-in-the-world-is-god-holy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/evidences/evil-problem-of-theodicy/evil-in-the-world-is-god-holy/</guid><description>&lt;p>Introduction: The Antilogism&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I. 	The origin of evil in the free will (intellect) of secondary agencies maintains the holiness of God.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>A. Persons involved&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Satan: John &lt;strong>&lt;sup>8&lt;/sup>&lt;/strong>:44&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Adam and Eve&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>a. Origin of sin among people: Romans &lt;strong>&lt;sup>15&lt;/sup>&lt;/strong>:12&lt;/p>
&lt;p>b. Universality among people&lt;/p>
&lt;p>B. Why allow evil in the first place?&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Evil is a necessary potentiality of free will. God is not limited by the option, but&lt;/p>
&lt;p>expresses himself in the option.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>GOOD AND EVIL IN ETERNAL PERSPECTIVE:</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/evidences/evil-problem-of-theodicy/good-and-evil-in-eternal-perspective/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/evidences/evil-problem-of-theodicy/good-and-evil-in-eternal-perspective/</guid><description>&lt;style>
